This paper is about text generation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The use of adversarial generative models and inverse reinforcement learning (IRL) also suggests a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Other possible sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) as text generation can also be applied to these areas.
